    public class List
extends ScrollGridPane
    It is a ScrollGridPane that instantiates a javax.swing.JList<Object> object as scroll-able object.

    It uses the default model for its embedded object and lets it be populated in each element with DescrStruct objects or with simple text.

    In the first case the model is mapped on the content of the whole associated LiteralStruct object and will render the literal member of each object; and, furthermore, lets the list row have the id member as datum associated. The list object, in this case, is a "read only" object used typically as medium of choices to drive other data objects.

    In the second case the model uses, as source of data, the associated JotyDataBuffer, so it as as many rows as its record quantity: however the rendering, by default, is again based on the LiteralStruct object which is looked up by its id member value that matches the value of the buffer key field. (see ListTerm class for alternative way of rendering).

    See Also:
    ScrollGridPane, ListTerm, LiteralsCollection.DescrStruct, initVerboseLayout(), Serialized Form
